The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                            Wednesday , November 4 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            The City Diary
                A 13-year-old boy died after a truck hit his bicycle at the PK Biswas Road-BT Road crossing in Khardah on Tuesday evening. Police said Rishabh Mishra, who studied in a Barrackpore school, was returning home from a friends house when the mishap occurred. Witnesses told cops that Rishabh was standing beside the road divider to cross the western flank of BT Road. The truck swerved right to hit the bicycle. The boy was declared dead at BN Bose hospital.     A Trinamul Youth Congress demonstration at Esplanade disrupted traffic from 1.45pm to 4.50pm. The demonstration, initially planned for Metro Channel, spread to Dorina Crossing and the KC Das intersection. Traffic was brought to a standstill on Lenin Sarani, Esplanade East, CR Avenue and SN Banerjee Road. Two hundred and fifty protesters were arrested.    Two persons were injured in separate accidents in the city late on Monday and Tuesday afternoon. A 27-year-old home guard, Tapan Gayen, was knocked down by a minidor on Belvedere Road, near Alipore zoo, on Tuesday afternoon. He was treated at SSKM Hospital and discharged. The driver has been arrested. In the other accident, an unidentified person in his early thirties was knocked down by an unknown vehicle on APC Road late on Monday. He was admitted to RG Kar Hospital.    Nearly 100 members of the College Street Market Byabsayee Samity (Independent) blocked the College Street-Kesub Chandra Sen Street crossing for half an hour from 1pm to protest the delay in the re-construction of College Street market. The blockade was lifted after police intervened.    Residents of Rajendrapur on Kalyani Expressway thrashed a police driver and damaged a vehicle belonging to Bijpur police station after it hit Monoj Brahma, 19, on Tuesday evening. Brahma is stable.				                                                                                                                                                                
